# Alternative spelling of [[pìobaireachd]] using purely Latin letters with out the special "ì". Piobaireachd just means "piping" in the gaelic language. A piobaireachd is also a long piping tune made up of lots of different variations. The famous MacCrimmon's of Skye were very well-known for their piobaireachd compositions.